===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant-y|marr|y|}}

# <!--DefB-->To unite in wedlock or matrimony; to perform the ceremony of joining spouses, ostensibly for life; to constitute a marital union according to the laws or customs of the place.
#: ''A justice of the peace will '''marry''' Jones and Smith.''
# To dispose of in wedlock; to give away as wife.
#: ''The king is keen to '''marry''' his daughters to influential princes.''
# To take for husband or wife.
#: ''In some cultures, it is acceptable for an uncle to '''marry''' his niece.''
#<!--DefC--> Figuratively, to unite in the closest and most endearing relation.
#: ''The attempt to '''marry''' medieval plainsong with speed metal produced interesting results.''


